The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | International | Michael faces drug charge
                                                                                                                           17                                                                                      Michael faces drug charge
                            
	London, Aug. 12 (Reuters): British singer George Michael was charged today with possessing cannabis and driving under the influence of drink or drugs following a car crash early last month, London police said.        
	Michael, 47, who has had a series of run-ins with the law for recreational drug use, was released on bail to appear in court in London on August 24, a police statement added.                                                                                                                                                           
